      {
        "id": 3060970,
        "name": "Nicos Neocleous",
        "username": "Nicos_Neocleous",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/ecd19e/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2021-01-02T20:24:28.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"166970\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"166970\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Nice.  Never had a 72 CDP.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>It\u2019s actually a very fine but for whatever reason not at all talked about vintage for the reason. The 1972 Clos des Papes is the best Clos de Papes I ever drank. Four down, one to go, and each bottle just irresistible.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>It\u2019s very rare to see 1972 CdP around these days.  I remember a good friend generously opening a 1972 Chateau de Beaucastel red around 2008, along with a 1962.   It was still fresh and had 5-10+ more years of ageing to go.</p>",
